        <type>int32_t</type>
        <definition>typedef int32_t CompassHeading</definition>
        <argsstring></argsstring>
        <name>CompassHeading</name>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Represents an angle relative to get to a reference direction, e.g. (magnetic) north. The angle value is scaled linearly, such that a value of TRIG_MAX_ANGLE corresponds to 360 degrees or 2 PI radians. Thus, if heading towards north, north is 0, west is TRIG_MAX_ANGLE/4, south is TRIG_MAX_ANGLE/2, and so on. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
        </detaileddescription>
