    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>The Compass Service combines information from Pebble&apos;s accelerometer and magnetometer to automatically calibrate the compass and transform the raw magnetic field information into a <ref refid="group___compass_service_1gab55689ab750b772e4a435905407843c4" kindref="member">CompassHeading</ref>, that is an angle to north. It also provides magnetic north and information about its status and accuracy through the <ref refid="struct_compass_heading_data" kindref="compound">CompassHeadingData</ref> structure. The API is designed to also provide true north in a future release.</para>
<para>Note that not all platforms have compasses. To check for the presence of a compass at compile time for the current platform use the <computeroutput>PBL_COMPASS</computeroutput> define.</para>
<para>To learn more about the Compass Service and how to use it, read the <ulink url="https://developer.getpebble.com/guides/pebble-apps/sensors/magnetometer/">Determining Direction</ulink> guide.</para>
<para>For available code samples, see the <ulink url="https://github.com/pebble-examples/feature-compass">feature-compass</ulink> example. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
